body:
Thank you for [this handy patch](#4444) @bacongobbler. Quite often you don't know the domain name of Tiller until after it is deployed, so too late to easily change the certificate (though possible with a `cert-manager` private CA), and this option addresses that. The `--tls-hostname` option can be set at run time so that fixes that and enables tiller verification.

It would be helpful if there was a matching environment variable for `--tls-hostname` e.g. `TILLER_TLS_HOSTNAME`. That would allow the entire TLS configuration to be in the environment, without have to inject command line options in CI/CD tasks.

